1.10	1998_Winter_Olympics_medal_table	1998 Winter Olympics medal table	The 1998 Winter Olympics, officially known as the XVIII Olympic Winter Games, was a winter multi-sport event held in Nagano, Japan, from 7 to 22 February 1998. A total of 2,176 athletes representing 72 National Olympic Committees (NOCs) participated in 68 events from 14 sports and disciplines. Curling and snowboarding were newly added sports for the 1998 Games, and women's ice hockey made its first appearance in the Olympics. Twenty-four NOCs earned medals at these Games, and fifteen won at least one gold medal.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6d/1998_Winter_Olympics_medals.JPG/220px-1998_Winter_Olympics_medals.JPG
